        "rich_text_7bxGmb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How Many Types of Diamonds Are There in the World of Modern Jewelry?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>How Many Types of Diamonds Are There in the World of Modern Jewelry?</h2>",
            "custom_id": "how-many",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_gB8tne": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/4C_39af316b-062b-445b-8caa-e281a445e05a.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Ultimately, knowing how many types of diamond there are helps you make a better choice for your jewelry. The scientific type influences the 4Cs, which in turn dictate the perfect application for a stone in a piece of fine jewelry from Lucira.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_CNg3En": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Matching a Diamond Type to Your Lucira Ring or Earrings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Matching a Diamond Type to Your Lucira Ring or Earrings</h3><p>The superior purity of Type IIa lab-grown diamonds makes them ideal for any jewelry piece where brilliance is key. When considering how many types of diamond would suit your style, purity is a great place to start.</p><p>Rings: For engagement and wedding rings, a brilliant, colorless Type IIa diamond from Lucira provides a timeless sparkle.<br/> Earrings & Necklaces: Their flawless appearance is perfect for studs, hoops, and pendants that catch the light with every movement, including romantic designs like our<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/rose-gold-diamond-necklace\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">rose gold diamond necklace</span></a>.<br/> Modern Mangalsutras & Bracelets: Durability and beauty make them perfect for pieces worn daily as an expression of self.</p>",
            "custom_id": "matching",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_fAE49y": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Impact of Diamond Cut and Shape on Brilliance and Style",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Impact of Diamond Cut and Shape on Brilliance and Style</h2>",
            "custom_id": "the-impact",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_VEj7TG": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/The_Impact_of_Diamond_Cut_and_Shape_on_Brilliance_and_Style_Updated.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_EaFUCR": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>For many, the answer to what are the different types of diamonds is about shape. The cut is what unlocks a diamond's fire and brilliance, and it's a critical part of its personality. <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Lucira</span></a> offers a range of popular shapes and exclusive cuts to match your personal style.</p><p>1.]Popular Shapes: Round, Princess, Oval, Emerald, Pear, Cushion.<br/>2.]Lucira Settings: Showcase your chosen diamond in a Solitaire, Halo, Toi et Moi, or Trilogy setting to create a truly unique piece that reflects you.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        }
